WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.879 --> 00:00:09.439
Earth.

2
00:00:09.441 --> 00:00:11.141
Fire.

3
00:00:11.143 --> 00:00:12.676
Air.

4
00:00:12.678 --> 00:00:14.878
Water.

5
00:00:14.880 --> 00:00:19.116
Only the Avatar can master all four elements

6
00:00:19.118 --> 00:00:21.852
and bring balance to the world.

7
00:00:24.857 --> 00:00:27.124
Sync & corrections by wilson0804
Resync by Metal Warrior 
 Addic7ed.com

8
00:00:27.126 --> 00:00:29.259
The world has entered a new age.

9
00:00:29.261 --> 00:00:31.495
Harmonic convergence created an energy shift

10
00:00:31.497 --> 00:00:34.431
the likes of which has
never been felt before.

11
00:00:34.433 --> 00:00:35.732
And after two weeks.

12
00:00:35.734 --> 00:00:37.134
Republic City continues to recover

13
00:00:37.136 --> 00:00:39.670
from Korra's epic battle with Unavaatu.

14
00:00:39.672 --> 00:00:41.605
Vines have sprouted up all over.

15
00:00:41.607 --> 00:00:42.840
creating pockets of wilds

16
00:00:42.842 --> 00:00:44.741
the spirits have come to call home.

17
00:00:44.743 --> 00:00:47.010
What other changes are
in store for our city?

18
00:00:57.650 --> 00:00:58.880
Come back. Bum-Ju.

19
00:01:03.890 --> 00:01:06.050
If you don't wanna wear
the sweater I made you.

20
00:01:06.060 --> 00:01:07.360
that's fine.

21
00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:09.420
I'm sorry I got mad.

22
00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:14.300
Bum-Ju. I'm running out of tree.

23
00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:18.170
Can we go down now?

24
00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:22.940
Bum-Ju. a little help?

25
00:01:24.310 --> 00:01:25.870
Ah! Ahh!

26
00:01:34.550 --> 00:01:35.980
Look!

27
00:01:35.990 --> 00:01:38.920
I'm airbending.

28
00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:40.320
Ah!

29
00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:43.160
Wow. that still hurt a lot.

30
00:01:56.510 --> 00:01:59.570
How are we ever gonna
clear away all these vines?

31
00:02:10.277 --> 00:02:11.320
I don't get it!

32
00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:14.590
I can vanquish Vaatu.
but not a bunch of stupid vines?

33
00:02:14.590 --> 00:02:16.830
I'm sure you'll find a way.

34
00:02:16.830 --> 00:02:18.290
Why do you wanna get rid of them?

35
00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:20.360
You changed the world.

36
00:02:20.360 --> 00:02:22.400
We're connected with the spirits again.

37
00:02:22.400 --> 00:02:24.230
The wilds are their home.

38
00:02:24.230 --> 00:02:26.040
I don't think the people
who used to live here

39
00:02:26.040 --> 00:02:28.640
are as excited about it as you are.

40
00:02:34.880 --> 00:02:37.210
I gotta go face the press and tell them

41
00:02:37.210 --> 00:02:39.480
I still don't have a way
to get rid of the vines.

42
00:02:39.480 --> 00:02:41.320
This should be fun.

43
00:02:44.950 --> 00:02:46.720
Mr. President.

44
00:02:46.720 --> 00:02:48.990
are you concerned that your approval ratings

45
00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:51.830
are now nearly as low as the Avatar's?

46
00:02:51.830 --> 00:02:53.530
Have you seen today's headline?

47
00:02:53.530 --> 00:02:58.170
It says. "Raik-oh-no. Polls pan Prez plans!"

48
00:02:58.170 --> 00:03:00.970
I'm not concerned with snappy
put-downs in the press.

49
00:03:00.970 --> 00:03:04.010
I'm facing this calamity just
like every other citizen.

50
00:03:04.010 --> 00:03:06.470
There's a tree growing
right through my office.

51
00:03:06.480 --> 00:03:08.140
You think I'm not doing everything I can

52
00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:09.610
to get rid of it?

53
00:03:11.980 --> 00:03:14.020
- A few questions. please!
- Avatar Korra!

54
00:03:14.020 --> 00:03:16.380
Do you regret the way you
handled the Unalaq crisis?

55
00:03:16.390 --> 00:03:18.690
Why are you forcing the
integration of spirits

56
00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:20.190
in Republic City?

57
00:03:20.190 --> 00:03:22.490
Listen.
I've been trying everything I can think of

58
00:03:22.490 --> 00:03:23.960
to get rid of these vines. but...

59
00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:26.430
- why can't you fix this?
- Are the vines here to stay?

60
00:03:26.430 --> 00:03:28.760
Is this part of your new world order?

61
00:03:28.770 --> 00:03:30.070
Look!

62
00:03:30.070 --> 00:03:32.570
Harmonic convergence was
just a couple weeks ago.

63
00:03:32.570 --> 00:03:34.270
I just need a little more time

64
00:03:34.270 --> 00:03:36.000
to get everything back to normal.

65
00:03:36.010 --> 00:03:39.370
The Avatar has put us all in
a very difficult position.

66
00:03:39.380 --> 00:03:41.280
- but my administration...
- Oh!

67
00:03:41.280 --> 00:03:42.440
I'm sorry.

68
00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:43.950
Did I put you in a difficult position

69
00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:46.350
by fighting the giant force of pure evil

70
00:03:46.350 --> 00:03:48.580
that was going to destroy the whole world?

71
00:03:48.590 --> 00:03:51.420
Maybe your administration
could've handled that!

72
00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:53.090
That's all! No more questions!

73
00:03:57.590 --> 00:03:59.060
This is a disaster.

74
00:03:59.060 --> 00:04:01.000
Don't worry. We'll figure something out.

75
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:02.600
Easy for you to say.

76
00:04:02.600 --> 00:04:04.630
You don't have my poll numbers.

77
00:04:04.630 --> 00:04:06.730
8% approval?

78
00:04:06.740 --> 00:04:08.040
Who were they asking?

79
00:04:08.040 --> 00:04:09.400
You can't take that to heart.

80
00:04:09.410 --> 00:04:10.710
People are just frustrated.

81
00:04:10.710 --> 00:04:12.210
I don't blame them.

82
00:04:12.210 --> 00:04:14.110
I should be able to fix this.

83
00:04:14.110 --> 00:04:16.110
I'm the Avatar.

84
00:04:20.780 --> 00:04:22.950
You are not gonna believe
what just happened.

85
00:04:22.950 --> 00:04:24.920
Where's your father?

86
00:04:24.920 --> 00:04:27.060
Dad!

87
00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:29.620
What is it? What's wrong?

88
00:04:29.630 --> 00:04:34.100
The most amazing. wondrous.
fantastical thing just occurred.

89
00:04:34.100 --> 00:04:36.060
Okay. Bum-Ju and I had a little fight.

90
00:04:36.070 --> 00:04:38.100
I made him this sweater.
and he didn't seem to like it.

91
00:04:38.100 --> 00:04:39.700
And I'll admit it might need work.

92
00:04:39.700 --> 00:04:41.840
but it was my first attempt at knitting.

93
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:43.540
So I was a little hurt.

94
00:04:43.540 --> 00:04:45.610
Hilarious.

95
00:04:45.610 --> 00:04:47.510
Time for dinner. everyone.

96
00:04:47.510 --> 00:04:50.150
No! Check this out.

97
00:04:50.150 --> 00:04:52.710
I can airbend!

98
00:04:55.150 --> 00:04:57.190
Yeah. wait. Seriously. I was doing it.

99
00:04:58.790 --> 00:05:00.560
Oh. hold on. I just...

100
00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:02.012
Maybe if I...

101
00:05:02.290 --> 00:05:03.460
No.

102
00:05:03.460 --> 00:05:07.100
I swear I'm not making it up.

103
00:05:10.770 --> 00:05:12.900
Stop waving your arms around at the table.

104
00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:14.400
It's not funny anymore.

105
00:05:14.400 --> 00:05:16.300
It's not a joke.

106
00:05:16.310 --> 00:05:17.840
What's up with him?

107
00:05:18.839 --> 00:05:20.110
Bumi says he airbended earlier.

108
00:05:20.110 --> 00:05:21.510
but he can't now.

109
00:05:21.510 --> 00:05:23.340
Oh. and I guess he's not
very good at knitting either.

110
00:05:23.350 --> 00:05:26.280
I gotta say.
I love being a part of this family.

111
00:05:26.280 --> 00:05:28.380
You got the grumpy dad. the wacky Uncle.

112
00:05:28.390 --> 00:05:30.320
The put-upon mom. crazy kids.

113
00:05:30.320 --> 00:05:33.050
This is great. Where's Mako?

114
00:05:33.060 --> 00:05:35.090
Oh. you mean the brooding teenager?

115
00:05:35.090 --> 00:05:36.930
He's staying at the police station.

116
00:05:36.930 --> 00:05:38.090
Still?

117
00:05:38.090 --> 00:05:39.890
I told him Tenzin invited us to stay here

118
00:05:39.900 --> 00:05:42.130
since our apartment is a vine habitat now.

119
00:05:42.130 --> 00:05:44.970
but he said he had to focus on work.

120
00:05:47.940 --> 00:05:49.600
Oh! Did you see that?

121
00:05:49.610 --> 00:05:51.140
I think the napkin moved.

122
00:05:51.140 --> 00:05:52.510
You blew on it.

123
00:05:52.510 --> 00:05:53.810
Wait!

124
00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:56.980
Maybe I can only do it
when my life is in danger.

125
00:05:56.980 --> 00:06:00.420
Bolin. bend a giant boulder at me.

126
00:06:00.420 --> 00:06:02.680
Yeah. I don't think that's a good idea.

127
00:06:02.690 --> 00:06:04.390
If you're gonna be bending giant boulders.

128
00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:05.690
you can do it outside.

129
00:06:05.690 --> 00:06:07.620
No one is bending giant boulders!

130
00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:09.460
Look alive. Uncle Bumi!

131
00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:12.490
Ah!

132
00:06:14.530 --> 00:06:18.100
I told you!

133
00:06:20.340 --> 00:06:22.470
Unbelievable.

134
00:06:22.470 --> 00:06:24.210
You're actually an airbender.

135
00:06:24.210 --> 00:06:28.680
Wait until I tell mom.
She's gonna love this.

136
00:06:37.650 --> 00:06:39.810
Ow!

137
00:06:43.880 --> 00:06:46.190
Police.

138
00:06:46.190 --> 00:06:49.720
He what? Slow down.

139
00:06:49.720 --> 00:06:52.020
Okay. I'm on my way.

140
00:06:55.600 --> 00:06:57.700
What the heck did all this?

141
00:06:57.700 --> 00:07:00.700
It was my brother. He's out of control!

142
00:07:00.700 --> 00:07:02.840
Okay. just tell me what happened.

143
00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:04.800
We were arguing about the books.

144
00:07:04.810 --> 00:07:06.840
and Daw was yelling at me.

145
00:07:06.840 --> 00:07:09.280
and all of a sudden things
started flying around!

146
00:07:09.280 --> 00:07:11.380
He was creating this storm like...

147
00:07:11.380 --> 00:07:12.710
Like what?

148
00:07:12.710 --> 00:07:14.480
Well. like he was airbending.

149
00:07:15.780 --> 00:07:18.380
Sir... That's impossible.

150
00:07:18.390 --> 00:07:20.950
There are only five airbenders
in the entire world.

151
00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:23.090
and your brother is not one of them.

152
00:07:23.090 --> 00:07:24.390
I know what I saw.

153
00:07:24.390 --> 00:07:27.260
He was freaking out. yelling.
"what's happening to me?"

154
00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:29.300
Then. he ran into the back room

155
00:07:29.300 --> 00:07:33.400
and locked himself in.

156
00:07:33.400 --> 00:07:36.040
Police. Open up.

157
00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:37.700
Go away!

158
00:07:37.710 --> 00:07:40.970
Get out here. sir.
or I'm knocking this door down.

159
00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:42.840
One...

160
00:07:42.840 --> 00:07:44.180
Two...

161
00:07:45.810 --> 00:07:49.050
Ah! I'm so sorry!

162
00:07:53.820 --> 00:07:57.060
I told you! Airbending!

163
00:08:00.930 --> 00:08:04.530
Ugh! I can't figure this thing out!

164
00:08:04.530 --> 00:08:06.370
Do you think being in the spirit world

165
00:08:06.370 --> 00:08:07.870
during harmonic convergence

166
00:08:07.870 --> 00:08:09.200
could've given him bending?

167
00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:11.070
I suppose it's possible.

168
00:08:11.070 --> 00:08:13.540
Maybe Uncle Bumi is just a late bloomer.

169
00:08:13.540 --> 00:08:17.480
I have been noticing a
change in your aura lately.

170
00:08:17.480 --> 00:08:20.110
And you didn't tell me?

171
00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:27.990
Invisible spirit monster attack?

172
00:08:27.990 --> 00:08:29.890
Lin! You won't believe this.

173
00:08:29.890 --> 00:08:33.130
Bumi just started airbending.

174
00:08:33.130 --> 00:08:34.990
I'm afraid he's not the only one.

175
00:08:35.000 --> 00:08:36.200
What?

176
00:08:36.200 --> 00:08:37.800
I got a call last night

177
00:08:37.800 --> 00:08:40.570
about a guy who just started
airbending out of nowhere.

178
00:08:40.570 --> 00:08:43.370
You mean there's another one?
Where is he now?

179
00:08:43.370 --> 00:08:46.810
He... Blew a door down on me and got away.

180
00:08:46.810 --> 00:08:49.380
We've got an all-points
bulletin out on him right now.

181
00:08:49.380 --> 00:08:51.310
Wait. we'll help you look for him.

182
00:08:51.310 --> 00:08:52.680
Where should we start?

183
00:08:52.680 --> 00:08:54.780
Oh. well. you know. you should...

184
00:08:54.780 --> 00:08:56.280
You should leave it to the police.

185
00:08:56.280 --> 00:08:58.380
It's... Police business. you know.

186
00:08:58.390 --> 00:09:01.990
It's. um... Official.

187
00:09:01.990 --> 00:09:03.420
Okay.

188
00:09:03.420 --> 00:09:05.090
How are you doing?

189
00:09:05.090 --> 00:09:06.590
You know you're welcome to stay here

190
00:09:06.590 --> 00:09:08.490
instead of sleeping at the police station.

191
00:09:09.730 --> 00:09:11.730
No. I'm fine.

192
00:09:11.730 --> 00:09:14.830
I should just get... Going.

193
00:09:14.840 --> 00:09:17.140
So!

194
00:09:17.140 --> 00:09:19.170
As you were...

195
00:09:19.170 --> 00:09:21.110
Ladies.

196
00:09:25.750 --> 00:09:27.710
This is so exciting!

197
00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:29.120
New airbenders in the city?

198
00:09:29.120 --> 00:09:32.420
I bet we can find that guy before Mako does.

199
00:09:32.420 --> 00:09:34.450
You know I'm not very good at this.

200
00:09:34.460 --> 00:09:37.620
You're the Avatar.
master of all the elements.

201
00:09:37.630 --> 00:09:39.430
You should know how to drive.

202
00:09:39.430 --> 00:09:41.960
Besides. it's relaxing.

203
00:09:42.909 --> 00:09:44.900
Clutch! Clutch!

204
00:09:44.900 --> 00:09:47.300
Ugh! Ah! Ugh!

205
00:09:49.440 --> 00:09:51.070
That's the brake.

206
00:09:51.070 --> 00:09:53.540
Let's try again. You ready?

207
00:09:57.350 --> 00:09:58.840
How long do you think talking to Mako

208
00:09:58.850 --> 00:10:00.750
is going to be like pulling teeth?

209
00:10:00.750 --> 00:10:02.380
Well. Mako has never been

210
00:10:02.380 --> 00:10:05.250
the most "in touch with his feelings" guy.

211
00:10:05.250 --> 00:10:07.590
But it'll get better eventually.

212
00:10:07.590 --> 00:10:09.590
So when I was gone.

213
00:10:09.590 --> 00:10:11.090
did he tell you that we broke up?

214
00:10:11.090 --> 00:10:13.960
Yeah. We all knew.

215
00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:15.390
Sorry.

216
00:10:15.400 --> 00:10:16.760
That's pretty embarrassing.

217
00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:19.130
Actually.
I need to tell you something about that.

218
00:10:19.130 --> 00:10:21.170
and I should've told you this sooner.

219
00:10:21.170 --> 00:10:24.340
but... While you were gone.

220
00:10:24.340 --> 00:10:27.440
I...Kind of... Kissed him.

221
00:10:27.440 --> 00:10:28.770
I'm sorry.

222
00:10:30.180 --> 00:10:32.140
No wonder he's so nervous around us.

223
00:10:32.150 --> 00:10:34.150
- You're not mad?
- No!

224
00:10:34.150 --> 00:10:36.820
I mean. I kissed Mako when he
was going out with you. so.

225
00:10:36.820 --> 00:10:38.150
You what?

226
00:10:38.150 --> 00:10:40.050
I'm so sorry! I thought you knew!

227
00:10:40.050 --> 00:10:42.990
I'm just kidding. I knew a long time ago.

228
00:10:44.290 --> 00:10:45.690
Well. whatever happened with Mako

229
00:10:45.690 --> 00:10:47.360
I'm glad it hasn't come between us.

230
00:10:47.360 --> 00:10:49.260
I've never had a girlfriend to hang out with

231
00:10:49.260 --> 00:10:50.830
and talk to before.

232
00:10:50.830 --> 00:10:52.360
except for Naga.

233
00:10:52.370 --> 00:10:53.830
This is nice.

234
00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.330
Vine! Vine!

235
00:11:01.110 --> 00:11:03.180
Hey! Watch where you're going!

236
00:11:03.180 --> 00:11:04.780
What are you doing living
in the middle of the road

237
00:11:04.780 --> 00:11:06.180
in the first place?

238
00:11:06.180 --> 00:11:07.680
Don't ask me. Avatar.

239
00:11:07.680 --> 00:11:09.120
You made the world this way.

240
00:11:09.120 --> 00:11:10.480
We're just living in it.

241
00:11:10.490 --> 00:11:12.750
Look. I don't have anything against spirits.

242
00:11:12.750 --> 00:11:14.750
but these vines are causing major problems

243
00:11:14.760 --> 00:11:16.160
all over the city.

244
00:11:16.160 --> 00:11:18.320
Spirits? Vines?

245
00:11:18.330 --> 00:11:19.790
We're all the same.

246
00:11:19.790 --> 00:11:22.930
Seems like the Avatar would know that.

247
00:11:24.830 --> 00:11:27.530
Korra. you okay?

248
00:11:27.540 --> 00:11:29.600
I think that spirit just gave me an idea

249
00:11:29.600 --> 00:11:31.440
how to get rid of these vines.

250
00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:33.940
But I'm gonna need a lot of water.

251
00:11:35.680 --> 00:11:38.180
It's like a dream. dad.

252
00:11:38.180 --> 00:11:41.980
After 170 years. new airbenders.

253
00:11:41.980 --> 00:11:44.150
Dad?

254
00:11:44.150 --> 00:11:45.720
When a new guy gets airbending.

255
00:11:45.720 --> 00:11:47.390
does that make him our brother?

256
00:11:47.390 --> 00:11:50.490
Well. in a way.
all airbenders are our family.

257
00:11:50.490 --> 00:11:51.960
Does that mean I have to share my room?

258
00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:53.730
Because I like my personal space.

259
00:11:53.730 --> 00:11:55.530
Of course not.

260
00:11:55.530 --> 00:11:57.000
But we might have to get used

261
00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:59.630
to not being the only
airbenders around any more.

262
00:11:59.630 --> 00:12:02.840
I hope we have enough for an army.

263
00:12:02.840 --> 00:12:05.640
I wanna be a commander like Uncle Bumi.

264
00:12:05.640 --> 00:12:07.940
Air nomads don't have armies. Meelo.

265
00:12:07.940 --> 00:12:11.510
But maybe there will be enough
to fill the temples again.

266
00:12:11.510 --> 00:12:13.410
What's wrong. daddy?

267
00:12:13.410 --> 00:12:16.650
I just wish your grandfather
were here to see this.

268
00:12:16.650 --> 00:12:19.080
Will you be airbender president?

269
00:12:19.090 --> 00:12:20.390
No.

270
00:12:20.390 --> 00:12:21.850
But I think the new airbenders

271
00:12:21.860 --> 00:12:23.290
will need lots of help and guidance

272
00:12:23.290 --> 00:12:26.960
to understand what it means
to be a part of our nation.

273
00:12:26.960 --> 00:12:29.030
That's a big responsibility.

274
00:12:29.030 --> 00:12:31.130
Don't worry. dad. We'll help you.

275
00:12:32.430 --> 00:12:36.400
I know you will.

276
00:12:40.810 --> 00:12:44.980
I hope this works.

277
00:12:44.980 --> 00:12:46.810
What are you guys doing here?

278
00:12:46.810 --> 00:12:48.810
I was alerted that you had a new plan

279
00:12:48.820 --> 00:12:50.780
to wipe out these noxious weeds.

280
00:12:50.790 --> 00:12:53.620
so I thought you'd want
everyone to be here to watch.

281
00:12:53.620 --> 00:12:54.820
Avatar Korra!

282
00:12:54.820 --> 00:12:56.660
Do you really think... No questions!

283
00:12:56.660 --> 00:13:00.030
Just stand there. Silently!

284
00:13:46.670 --> 00:13:48.776
Go in peace.

285
00:13:50.410 --> 00:13:52.210
How did you know what to do?

286
00:13:52.210 --> 00:13:53.680
Will you send the spirits away now?

287
00:13:53.680 --> 00:13:56.080
How soon can we expect public
water service to resume?

288
00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:12.360
Look out!

289
00:14:23.180 --> 00:14:25.010
Let's go. people. Hurry!

290
00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:38.960
Hang on!

291
00:14:56.610 --> 00:14:58.610
I think that could've gone better.

292
00:15:05.980 --> 00:15:07.660
Can't talk. Meditating.

293
00:15:08.050 --> 00:15:11.320
You must be at the end of your rope.
You hate meditating.

294
00:15:12.180 --> 00:15:13.570
I thought that if I really tried.

295
00:15:13.590 --> 00:15:16.190
I might be able to contact
my past Avatars.

296
00:15:16.210 --> 00:15:18.910
Someone who knows something
to help me.

297
00:15:18.930 --> 00:15:19.900
But I can't.

298
00:15:20.430 --> 00:15:22.660
They're gone and I'm all alone.

299
00:15:24.430 --> 00:15:27.440
Did I ruin everything by leaving
the spirit portals open?

300
00:15:27.850 --> 00:15:29.980
You didn't ruin anything.

301
00:15:30.010 --> 00:15:32.260
You did what you thought was best
for the world.

302
00:15:32.670 --> 00:15:34.710
And now things have changed.

303
00:15:34.740 --> 00:15:37.100
Change can be good or bad.

304
00:15:37.130 --> 00:15:38.740
depending on your point of view.

305
00:15:40.060 --> 00:15:42.100
I know the people's point of view.

306
00:15:42.120 --> 00:15:44.730
- It's bad.
- You're not the president. Korra.

307
00:15:45.330 --> 00:15:47.370
Your job isn't to fix the daily problems

308
00:15:47.400 --> 00:15:49.570
of every person in Republic City.

309
00:15:50.290 --> 00:15:54.390
Your responsibility is to bring balance
to the entire world.

310
00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:56.360
And that means no matter
what you do.

311
00:15:56.390 --> 00:15:59.000
some people are not going to be
happy about it.

312
00:15:59.120 --> 00:15:59.930
Great.

313
00:16:00.120 --> 00:16:03.110
On the other hand. some people will be
very happy.

314
00:16:03.440 --> 00:16:04.330
like me.

315
00:16:04.730 --> 00:16:07.070
What you did during Harmonic Convergence.

316
00:16:07.090 --> 00:16:08.890
may have brought back the Air Nation.

317
00:16:09.340 --> 00:16:11.880
And that can only be good for
restoring balance.

318
00:16:12.160 --> 00:16:15.110
That is the act of a great Avatar.

319
00:16:15.130 --> 00:16:16.450
It's scary.

320
00:16:16.480 --> 00:16:20.100
I have all this power and all these
people depending on me.

321
00:16:20.130 --> 00:16:22.790
but I don't know what I'm supposed
to be doing half the time.

322
00:16:23.210 --> 00:16:26.250
It seems like I should be wiser.

323
00:16:26.520 --> 00:16:30.030
True wisdom begins when we accept
things as they are.

324
00:16:30.510 --> 00:16:32.260
You started a new age Korra.

325
00:16:32.280 --> 00:16:34.410
there's no going back to the past.

326
00:16:35.100 --> 00:16:37.400
Mako called. the cops found
the new airbender guy.

327
00:16:37.430 --> 00:16:38.530
But when they try to bring him in.

328
00:16:38.550 --> 00:16:40.740
he ran away and climbed to the top
of Kyoshi bridge

329
00:16:40.780 --> 00:16:41.810
and he won't come down.

330
00:16:42.570 --> 00:16:45.370
Uh... Sorry. did I interrupt an Avatar
wisdom session?

331
00:16:46.470 --> 00:16:49.180
Avatar wisdom is a thing
of the past. Bolin. Come on.

332
00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:50.350
Oh. Okay.

333
00:16:50.840 --> 00:16:51.760
Is that a good thing?

334
00:16:51.960 --> 00:16:53.410
Depends who you ask.

335
00:17:05.230 --> 00:17:08.390
Come down immediately or we will be forced
to take action.

336
00:17:11.170 --> 00:17:13.690
Stay back! I'm dangerous.

337
00:17:19.690 --> 00:17:21.340
Sorry!

338
00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:38.290
Don't panic. I'm just here to talk.

339
00:17:38.590 --> 00:17:42.230
Please. I don't know what I'm doing
and I don't wanna hurt anyone.

340
00:17:42.620 --> 00:17:45.260
Tell me about it. Rough day. huh?

341
00:17:45.450 --> 00:17:47.200
I'm having kind of a rough day myself.

342
00:17:47.270 --> 00:17:48.860
You mind if I sit down here?

343
00:17:49.780 --> 00:17:51.960
- No.
- I know you're scared.

344
00:17:52.150 --> 00:17:55.780
You've gone through a big change and
it's kind of my fault.

345
00:17:56.660 --> 00:18:00.120
But you're not alone. There are other
airbenders and they want to help you.

346
00:18:00.370 --> 00:18:02.530
Actually. they're really excited to meet you.

347
00:18:02.800 --> 00:18:04.680
I don't want to be an airbender.

348
00:18:04.710 --> 00:18:07.510
Please. you're the Avatar. make it stop.

349
00:18:08.990 --> 00:18:11.040
I'm sorry. I can't.

350
00:18:11.450 --> 00:18:13.550
But I promise you. things will get better

351
00:18:13.570 --> 00:18:15.010
if you just give it a chance.

352
00:18:15.810 --> 00:18:18.870
Let me take you over to Air Temple Island
and we can talk this through.

353
00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:19.790
okay?

354
00:18:37.270 --> 00:18:40.630
Daw. this is Tenzin.
He's going to help you.

355
00:18:40.880 --> 00:18:43.810
It is absolutely my pleasure
to meet you. Daw.

356
00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:46.690
I've never met a new airbender before.

357
00:18:46.720 --> 00:18:49.720
Well. at least not one whose diaper
I didn't have to change.

358
00:18:49.730 --> 00:18:51.830
Actually I just fell off a bridge

359
00:18:51.850 --> 00:18:54.530
so I could use a fresh diaper
right about now.

360
00:18:55.770 --> 00:18:57.290
So is this the deal.

361
00:18:57.560 --> 00:19:00.650
we have a crisis every other day now
thanks to you?

362
00:19:00.850 --> 00:19:03.810
Listen. I know you're having a tough time
getting used to these changes

363
00:19:03.830 --> 00:19:05.130
and I'm sorry for that.

364
00:19:05.450 --> 00:19:08.600
But you and everyone else are gonna
have to learn to live with it.

365
00:19:09.060 --> 00:19:11.730
The vines and the spirits are here to stay.

366
00:19:12.020 --> 00:19:13.690
Well. you know who's not here to stay?

367
00:19:13.740 --> 00:19:15.850
You! I order you to leave this city.

368
00:19:15.970 --> 00:19:18.160
You've caused nothing but trouble
since you arrived.

369
00:19:21.750 --> 00:19:24.300
Don't worry. I was already leaving.

370
00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:32.900
I can see my path now.

371
00:19:32.930 --> 00:19:35.220
There are new airbenders out there and
I'm gonna find them

372
00:19:35.240 --> 00:19:36.810
and rebuild the Air Nation.

373
00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:40.330
Don't think I'm not going with you.
It's so exciting.

374
00:19:40.510 --> 00:19:42.430
Who knows who's out there right now.

375
00:19:42.450 --> 00:19:45.620
discovering the gift of airbending for
the first time.

376
00:20:13.110 --> 00:20:15.160
You know the drill. Zaheer.

377
00:20:15.280 --> 00:20:16.280
Of course.

378
00:20:19.290 --> 00:20:20.880
I hope you still like rice.

379
00:20:21.850 --> 00:20:26.010
Have you ever read the poetry of
the great airbending guru. Lahima?

380
00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:26.870
What?

381
00:20:27.290 --> 00:20:31.910
Guru Lahima lived 4000 years ago
in the Northern Air Temple.

382
00:20:32.080 --> 00:20:35.140
It is said that he unlocked the secret of
weightlessness

383
00:20:35.180 --> 00:20:37.110
and became untethered from the earth.

384
00:20:37.390 --> 00:20:41.020
living his final 40 years without ever
touching the ground.

385
00:20:41.230 --> 00:20:43.050
Is that how you plan to escape.

386
00:20:43.080 --> 00:20:46.260
with something you picked up
from an old airbender children's story?

387
00:20:46.280 --> 00:20:50.720
Like all great children's tales.
it contains truth within the myth.

388
00:20:51.010 --> 00:20:54.090
Lahima once wrote. instinct is a lie.

389
00:20:54.140 --> 00:20:57.690
told by a fearful body hoping to be wrong.

390
00:20:57.810 --> 00:20:59.250
What's that supposed to mean?

391
00:20:59.310 --> 00:21:03.690
It means that when you base your
expectations only on what you see.

392
00:21:03.710 --> 00:21:08.220
you blind yourself to the possibilities
of a new reality.

393
00:21:14.290 --> 00:21:18.480
Unh unh unh. you wouldn't want to singe
your friend. would you?

394
00:21:18.530 --> 00:21:19.900
How?

395
00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:21.860
You're not a bender.

396
00:21:22.230 --> 00:21:24.620
Nature is constantly changing.

397
00:21:25.070 --> 00:21:26.260
like the wind.

398
00:21:54.700 --> 00:21:57.020
Now you might wanna ration that
bowl of rice.

399
00:21:57.610 --> 00:22:00.460
You've got 3 weeks until
the next shift change.

400
00:22:01.130 --> 00:22:02.990
It's the dawning of a new age.

401
00:22:03.230 --> 00:22:08.260
The end of the White Lotus and soon.
the end of the Avatar.

402
00:22:15.170 --> 00:22:20.280
